@startuml
skinparam defaultFontName "DejaVu Sans"
skinparam defaultFontSize 15
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign left
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
hide footbox

title Calibration feedback capability and submission
autonumber 1 "<b>[00]"

participant Browser
participant "Feedback API" as Feedback
database "Feedback store" as Store
participant "Cached location\nresolver" as Resolver
participant "Write limiter" as Limiter
participant Astronomy

group Capability is advisory, not a reservation
  Browser -> Feedback: GET /api/calibration-feedback/v1/capability
  Feedback -> Feedback: Map explicit feature setting\nand known dependency state
  Feedback --> Browser: 200 schemaVersion + serverTime\nfeatureState + submissionAvailability
  note over Browser, Feedback
    Always Cache-Control: no-store.
    The response exposes no cause, capacity, or count.
    Transient token exhaustion does not change capability.
  end note
end

Browser -> Browser: Tester opens feedback for the loaded real opportunity\nand enters at least one evidence field
Browser -> Browser: Copy locationId + opportunityId\nCreate lowercase UUIDv4; freeze normalized payload
Browser -> Feedback: POST /api/calibration-feedback/v1/submissions\nUTF-8 JSON, at most 16,384 received bytes
Feedback -> Feedback: Enforce media type, content encoding,\nand received-body bound

break Unsupported transport or oversized body
  Feedback --> Browser: 413 request_too_large\nor 415 unsupported_media_type
end
Feedback -> Feedback: Capture one receipt instant;\ntruncate immediately to microseconds
Feedback -> Feedback: Parse closed schema; validate and normalize;\nrequire ambient light, crescent visibility, or notes
break Invalid JSON or request
  Feedback --> Browser: 400 invalid_json or invalid_request
  Browser -> Browser: Show error summary; preserve safe input
end
break Invalid report
  Feedback --> Browser: 422 invalid_report
  Browser -> Browser: Show field error; preserve safe input
end

Feedback -> Feedback: Build exact five-slot frame;\nSHA-256 -> raw 32-byte digest
note over Browser, Feedback
  US-ASCII prefix: moon-service/calibration-feedback/idempotency/v1
  Slots, in order: normalized locationId, opportunityId,
  ambientLight?, crescentVisibility?, normalized notes?
  The first two slots are always present.
  Absent = 0x00
  Present = 0x01 + unsigned uint32 big-endian UTF-8 length + UTF-8 bytes
  Values are parsed and normalized, never raw JSON bytes.
  No prefix terminator, separator, padding, BOM, or trailing byte.
  No other request or server value is hashed.
end note

break Feature disabled
  Feedback --> Browser: 503 feedback_unavailable
end
Feedback -> Store: lookup(clientSubmissionId)

break Found, same digest
  Store --> Feedback: Original serverReportId + submittedAt
  Feedback --> Browser: 200 replayed with original values
end
break Found, different digest
  Store --> Feedback: UUID belongs to different content
  Feedback --> Browser: 409 client_submission_conflict
end
break Store lookup disabled
  Store --> Feedback: Disabled
  Feedback --> Browser: 503 feedback_unavailable
end
break Store lookup unavailable
  Store --> Feedback: Unavailable
  Feedback --> Browser: 503 feedback_unavailable
  Browser -> Browser: Show generic unavailable; keep frozen payload
  Browser -> Feedback: If capability permits, tester explicitly retries\nthe same UUID and frozen normalized payload
end
Store --> Feedback: NotFound; continue
note over Feedback, Store
  Disabled feedback and every terminal lookup outcome
  stop before location resolution or token consumption.
end note

Feedback -> Store: status()
break Store disabled
  Store --> Feedback: Disabled
  Feedback --> Browser: 503 feedback_unavailable
end
break Store unavailable or full
  Store --> Feedback: Unavailable or full
  Feedback --> Browser: 503 feedback_unavailable
  Browser -> Browser: Show generic unavailable; keep frozen payload
  Browser -> Feedback: If capability permits, tester explicitly retries\nthe same UUID and frozen normalized payload
end
Store --> Feedback: Normal or near capacity; continue

Feedback -> Resolver: resolveLocationId(normalized locationId)
break Location not found
  Resolver --> Feedback: NotFound
  Feedback --> Browser: 422 location_not_found
end
break Resolver unavailable
  Resolver --> Feedback: Unavailable
  Feedback --> Browser: 503 feedback_unavailable
  Browser -> Browser: Show generic unavailable; keep frozen payload
  Browser -> Feedback: If capability permits, tester explicitly retries\nthe same UUID and frozen normalized payload
end
Resolver --> Feedback: Canonical backend ID + calculation input
note over Feedback, Resolver
  The report stores the canonical backend ID,
  not full city or coordinate data.
end note

Feedback -> Limiter: consume one instance-global write token
break Token exhausted
  Limiter --> Feedback: Retry delay
  Feedback --> Browser: 429 rate_limited + matching Retry-After
  Browser -> Browser: Show Retry-After; keep frozen payload
  Browser -> Feedback: After Retry-After, tester explicitly retries\nthe same UUID and frozen normalized payload
end
Limiter --> Feedback: Token admitted; continue
note over Limiter, Store
  Once admitted, the token is never restored after astronomy failure,
  a store failure, a capacity race, or a transactional replay/conflict.
end note

Feedback -> Astronomy: Compute at the normalized receipt instant
break Astronomy unavailable
  Astronomy --> Feedback: Failure
  Feedback --> Browser: 503 feedback_unavailable
  Browser -> Browser: Show generic unavailable; keep frozen payload
  Browser -> Feedback: If capability permits, tester explicitly retries\nthe same UUID and frozen normalized payload
end
Astronomy --> Feedback: Moon altitude + Moon illumination\nSun altitude + light bucket

Feedback -> Store: store UUID + raw digest + reduced report\ncanonical backend ID + receipt instant + four facts
Store -> Store: Transaction: recheck UUID/digest,\nthen capacity, then insert
break New row created
  Store --> Feedback: Created with new serverReportId
  Feedback --> Browser: 201 created + submittedAt
end
break Concurrent exact request won
  Store --> Feedback: Original serverReportId + submittedAt
  Feedback --> Browser: 200 replayed with original values
end
break Concurrent different request won
  Store --> Feedback: Conflict
  Feedback --> Browser: 409 client_submission_conflict
end
break Transactional store disabled
  Store --> Feedback: Disabled
  Feedback --> Browser: 503 feedback_unavailable
end
break Capacity race or store unavailable
  Store --> Feedback: Cannot store
  Feedback --> Browser: 503 feedback_unavailable
  Browser -> Browser: Show generic unavailable; keep frozen payload
  Browser -> Feedback: If capability permits, tester explicitly retries\nthe same UUID and frozen normalized payload
end

legend bottom
  **Cross-cutting unknown-outcome rule for every sent submission request**
  If no definite response arrives, show "Submission outcome unknown".
  The tester may explicitly resend the same UUID and frozen normalized payload.
  Never retry automatically. A committed row replays its original IDs and time.
  If no row exists, retry may create one at its later receipt instant.
  Any changed digest slot requires a new UUID.
endlegend

@enduml
